It works. Here's the full program targeting `net11.0`:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase
};

string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Output:**
```json
{"Name":"Alice","Age":30}
```

`JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` is a built-in policy (added alongside the existing `CamelCase`, `SnakeCaseLower`, `KebabCaseLower`, etc.) that uppercases the first letter of each word — exactly what you need to turn the lowercase positional-record parameters (`name`, `age`) into `Name` and `Age` in the JSON.
